description: This is Ungeria floribunda (Malvaceae or Sterculiaceae) the bastard oak of Norfolk Island. Now a very uncommon (threatened) tree of mid slope Norfolk Pine (Araucaria heterophylla) forest. Very rarely seen in flower now, and even more rarely seen setting seed. Ungeria is an endemic, Norfolk Island monotypic genus.
